Create a volume
\_Volume type : 
              \_General Purpose SSD(gp3)   *           >> Most workload        default ,cost effective     
              \_General Purpose SSD(gp2)               >> Legacy workload      IOPS depends on  volume size
              \_Provisioned IOPS SSD(io1)              >> High performance DB  Older Version 
              \_Provisioned IOPS SSD(io2)   *          >> Mission-Critical DB  Highest durability 
              \_Cold HDD(src1)                         >> Big data ,streaming  Highest throughput ,not IOPS
              \_Throughtput optimized HDD(st1)         >> Cold Storage         Cheapest
              \_Magnetic (standard) [HDD]              >> Legacy workload      Deprecated 

\_Size : What the size of the volume you need 
\_IOPS : How much read and write operation per second
\_ThroughPut : How much data transfered  [size] per second 
\_Availability_Zone :  Provuide the availability zone in which you want the volume 
\_Snapshot ID : Snapshot  ID is the backup you want to restore from 
\_Encrypt :   Enabel this to encrypt the volume
\_Tags: Provide the Tags 

Click on create VOLUME 

